<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,438,1437]" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">
After the Phalangopsidae’s taxonomic reorganization adopted by 
<bibRefCitation author="Cigliano, M. &amp; Braun, H. &amp; Eades, D. C. &amp; Otte, D." box="[930,1173,475,501]" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" refId="ref9519" refString="Cigliano, M. M, Braun, H., Eades, D. C. &amp; Otte, D. (2020) Orthoptera Species File Online. Version 5.0 / 5.0. Available from: http: // Orthoptera. SpeciesFile. org (accessed 20 December 2020)" type="url" year="2020">
Cigliano 
<emphasis box="[1034,1083,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">et al</emphasis>
. (2020)
</bibRefCitation>
, the subfamily presents now the greatest number of species cytogenetically studied, but all of them included in only two genera, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Saussure" authorityYear="1878" box="[1327,1436,511,537]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Endecous" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1327,1436,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">Endecous</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chopard" authorityYear="1956" box="[199,342,547,573]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Eidmanacris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[199,342,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">Eidmanacris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,438,1437]" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">
The 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Saussure" authorityYear="1878" box="[251,360,583,609]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Endecous" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[251,360,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">Endecous</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’ species present a complex model of chromosomal derivation, with a group of species with 2n = 19, and most M/SM chromosomes in the karyotype (
<taxonomicName authority="Souza-Dias &amp; de Mello, 2017" authorityName="Souza-Dias &amp; de Mello" authorityYear="2017" box="[768,1432,619,645]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Endecous" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chape" subGenus="Endecous">
<emphasis box="[768,877,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">Endecous</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[894,1003,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">Endecous</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1019,1086,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">chape</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Souza-Dias, P. G. B. &amp; Szinwelski, N. &amp; Fianco M. &amp; De Oliveira, E. C. &amp; de Mello, F. A. G. &amp; Zefa, E." box="[1093,1432,619,645]" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" pagination="454 - 470" refId="ref11136" refString="Souza-Dias, P. G. B., Szinwelski, N., Fianco M., De Oliveira, E. C., de Mello, F. A. G. &amp; Zefa, E. (2017) New species of Endecous (Grylloidea, Phalangopsidae, Luzarinae) from the Iguacu National Park (Brazil), including bioacoustics, cytogenetic and distribution data. Zootaxa, 4237 (3), 454 - 470. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4237.3.2" type="journal article" year="2017">Souza-Dias &amp; de Mello, 2017</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Berg" baseAuthorityYear="1891" box="[151,327,655,681]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Endecous" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="onthophagus">
<emphasis box="[151,327,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">E. onthophagus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Rehn, 1918" authorityName="Rehn" authorityYear="1918" box="[382,887,655,681]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Endecous" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="itatibensis" subGenus="Endecous">
<emphasis box="[382,491,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">Endecous</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[507,616,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">Endecous</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[633,748,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">itatibensis</emphasis>
Rehn, 1918
</taxonomicName>
), and another composed of species with 2n = 21, with the majority of A/T chromosomes (
<taxonomicName authority="de Mello &amp; Pellegatti-Franco, 1998" authorityName="de Mello &amp; Pellegatti-Franco" authorityYear="1998" box="[603,1382,691,717]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Endecous" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="betariensis" subGenus="Endecous">
<emphasis box="[603,712,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">Endecous</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[728,837,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">Endecous</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[853,976,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">betariensis</emphasis>
de Mello &amp; Pellegatti-Franco, 1998
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Zefa, 2010" authorityName="Zefa" authorityYear="2010" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Endecous" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alejomesai" subGenus="Endecous">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">Endecous</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[246,355,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">Endecous</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[372,493,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">alejomesai</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Zefa, E. &amp; Fontanetti, C. S. &amp; Martins, L. P." box="[501,623,727,753]" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" pagination="53 - 58" refId="ref11518" refString="Zefa, E., Fontanetti, C. S. &amp; Martins, L. P. (2010) Cytotaxonomy of the crickets Endecous Saussure, 1878 with an overview of the chromosomes of Phalangopsinae Group (Orthoptera: Phalangopsinae). Zootaxa, 2498 (1), 53 - 58. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 2498.1.4" type="journal article" year="2010">Zefa, 2010</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Costa Lima, 1940" authorityName="Costa Lima" authorityYear="1940" box="[679,1282,727,753]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Endecous" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cavernicolus" subGenus="Endecous">
<emphasis box="[679,788,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">Endecous</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[805,914,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">Endecous</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[930,1073,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">cavernicolus</emphasis>
Costa Lima, 1940
</taxonomicName>
). In addition, 
<taxonomicName authority="Castro-Souza et al., 2020" authorityName="Castro-Souza" authorityYear="2020" box="[151,830,763,789]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Endecous" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="troglobius" subGenus="Pedroecous">
<emphasis box="[151,260,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">Endecous</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[277,408,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">Pedroecous</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[424,538,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">troglobius</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Castro-Souza, R. A. &amp; Zefa, E. &amp; Ferreira, R. L." box="[545,830,763,789]" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" pagination="271 - 304" refId="ref9361" refString="Castro-Souza, R. A., Zefa, E. &amp; Ferreira, R. L. (2020) New troglobitic and troglophilic syntopic species of Endecous (Orthoptera, Grylloidea, Phalangopsidae) from a Brazilian cave: a case of sympatric speciation? Zootaxa, 4810 (2), 271 - 304. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4810.2.3" type="journal article" year="2020">
Castro-Souza 
<emphasis box="[703,760,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">et al.</emphasis>
, 2020
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Castro-Souza et al., 2020" authorityName="Castro-Souza" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Endecous" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="didymus" subGenus="Pedroecous">
<emphasis box="[885,994,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">Endecous</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1010,1141,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">Pedroecous</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1158,1251,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">didymus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Castro-Souza, R. A. &amp; Zefa, E. &amp; Ferreira, R. L." pageId="12" pageNumber="113" pagination="271 - 304" refId="ref9361" refString="Castro-Souza, R. A., Zefa, E. &amp; Ferreira, R. L. (2020) New troglobitic and troglophilic syntopic species of Endecous (Orthoptera, Grylloidea, Phalangopsidae) from a Brazilian cave: a case of sympatric speciation? Zootaxa, 4810 (2), 271 - 304. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4810.2.3" type="journal article" year="2020">
Castro-Souza 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">et al.</emphasis>
, 2020
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
also present 2n = 21♁, but with karyotypes bearing the majority of M/SM chromosomes. 
<taxonomicName authority="Zefa, 2014" authorityName="Zefa" authorityYear="2014" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Endecous" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ubajarensis" subGenus="Endecous">
<emphasis box="[1245,1354,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">Endecous</emphasis>
(
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">Endecous</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[218,348,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">ubajarensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Zefa, E. &amp; Redu, D. R. &amp; Costa, M. K. M. &amp; Gottschalk, M. S. &amp; Padilha, G. B. &amp; Silva, A. F. &amp; Martins, L. P." box="[355,476,835,861]" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" pagination="125 - 132" refId="ref11585" refString="Zefa, E., Redu, D. R., Costa, M. K. M., Gottschalk, M. S., Padilha, G. B., Silva, A. F. &amp; Martins, L. P. (2014) A new species of Endecous Saussure, 1878 (Orthoptera, Gryllidae) from northeast Brazil with the first X 1 X 20 chromosomal sex system in Gryllidae. Zootaxa, 3847 (1), 125 - 132. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3847.1.7" type="journal article" year="2014">Zefa, 2014</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
presents a high reduction in the chromosome number (2n = 14♁) probably due to two successive X/autosomes centric fusion to form the sex-determining system X 
<subScript attach="both" box="[1015,1023,889,903]" fontSize="6" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">1</subScript>
X 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1043,1051,889,903]" fontSize="6" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">2</subScript>
0♁ (
<bibRefCitation author="Zefa, E. &amp; Redu, D. R. &amp; Costa, M. K. M. &amp; Gottschalk, M. S. &amp; Padilha, G. B. &amp; Silva, A. F. &amp; Martins, L. P." box="[1101,1285,871,897]" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" pagination="125 - 132" refId="ref11585" refString="Zefa, E., Redu, D. R., Costa, M. K. M., Gottschalk, M. S., Padilha, G. B., Silva, A. F. &amp; Martins, L. P. (2014) A new species of Endecous Saussure, 1878 (Orthoptera, Gryllidae) from northeast Brazil with the first X 1 X 20 chromosomal sex system in Gryllidae. Zootaxa, 3847 (1), 125 - 132. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3847.1.7" type="journal article" year="2014">
Zefa 
<emphasis box="[1161,1218,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">et al.</emphasis>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,438,1437]" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">
The karyotype of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Berg" baseAuthorityYear="1891" box="[400,576,907,933]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Endecous" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="onthophagus">
<emphasis box="[400,576,907,933]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">E. onthophagus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[644,742,907,933]" name="Uruguay" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">Uruguay</collectingCountry>
was classified by 
<bibRefCitation author="Zefa, E. &amp; Fontanetti, C. S. &amp; Martins, L. P." box="[948,1145,907,933]" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" pagination="53 - 58" refId="ref11518" refString="Zefa, E., Fontanetti, C. S. &amp; Martins, L. P. (2010) Cytotaxonomy of the crickets Endecous Saussure, 1878 with an overview of the chromosomes of Phalangopsinae Group (Orthoptera: Phalangopsinae). Zootaxa, 2498 (1), 53 - 58. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 2498.1.4" type="journal article" year="2010">
Zefa 
<emphasis box="[1007,1056,907,933]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">et al</emphasis>
. (2010)
</bibRefCitation>
according to CI proposed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Guerra, M. S." box="[186,346,943,970]" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" pagination="741 - 743" refId="ref9850" refString="Guerra, M. S. (1986) Reviewing the chromosome nomenclature of Levan et al. Revista Brasileira de Genetica, 9, 741 - 743." type="journal article" year="1986">Guerra (1986)</bibRefCitation>
, and showed the pairs 4 and 5 acrocentrics. When reclassifying these homologous pairs according to 
<bibRefCitation author="Levan, A. &amp; Fredga, K. &amp; Sandberg, A. A." box="[180,395,979,1006]" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" pagination="201 - 220" refId="ref9923" refString="Levan, A., Fredga, K. &amp; Sandberg, A. A. (1964) Nomenclature for centromeric position of chromosomes. Hereditas, 52 (2), 201 - 220. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1601 - 5223.1964. tb 01953. x" type="journal article" year="1964">
Levan 
<emphasis box="[257,306,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">et al</emphasis>
. (1964)
</bibRefCitation>
we found the pair 4 is a submetacentric. In individuals from Pelotas/RS/ 
<collectingCountry box="[1212,1281,979,1005]" name="Brazil" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, pairs 4 and 5 are submetacentrics, showing that polymorphism occurs in pair 5 between individuals from both locations.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,438,1437]" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">
The irregular M/SM and A/T chromosomes distribution in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Saussure" authorityYear="1878" box="[888,997,1051,1077]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Endecous" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[888,997,1051,1077]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">Endecous</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species karyotypes, together with the variation in the FN shows that the chromosomal derivation in these species occurred with a predominance of pericentric inversions, and/or other type of rearrangements that occurs independently in each of these species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,438,1437]" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">
The chromosomal derivation in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Desutter-Grandcolas" authorityYear="1994" box="[573,750,1159,1185]" class="Polychaeta" family="Oenonidae" genus="Laranda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Eunicida" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="meridionalis">
<emphasis box="[573,750,1159,1185]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">E. meridionalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sperber" authorityYear="1998" box="[812,952,1159,1185]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Eidmanacris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bidentata">
<emphasis box="[812,952,1159,1185]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">E. bidentata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
points to a path in which the karyotypes reached the end of the chromosomal derivation by successive centric fusions, showed by the low number of chromosomes in the karyotypes, all of them M/SMs. However, a subsequent step to centric fusions was the occurrence of pericentric inversions adding to the karyotype of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Desutter-Grandcolas" authorityYear="1995" box="[754,954,1267,1293]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Eidmanacris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="septentrionalis">
<emphasis box="[754,954,1267,1293]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">E. septentrionalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1014,1197,1267,1293]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Eidmanacris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alboannulata">
<emphasis box="[1014,1197,1267,1293]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">E. alboannulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
acrocentric chromosomes (pairs 5 and 6, and pair 2, respectively), which are approximately the same size as the other chromosomes of the karyotype. 
<taxonomicName box="[321,602,1339,1365]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Eidmanacris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="corumbatai">
<emphasis box="[321,602,1339,1365]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">Eidmanacris corumbatai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
deserves special attention, as pericentric inversions gave the karyotype a greater number of acrocentric chromosomes, preserving the low chromosome number in the karyotype (
<bibRefCitation author="Mesa, A. &amp; Sperber, C. F. &amp; Garcia, P. C." pageId="12" pageNumber="113" pagination="43 - 61" refId="ref10197" refString="Mesa, A., Sperber, C. F. &amp; Garcia, P. C. (1998) Two new species of the cricket genus Eidmanacris and a new combination name for a third species (Orthoptera, Grylloidea, Phalangopsidae). Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 124, 43 - 61." type="journal article" year="1998">
Mesa 
<emphasis box="[1381,1437,1375,1401]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">et al.</emphasis>
1998
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
